WEBVTT

00:10.910 --> 00:12.479
[indistinct chatter]

00:12.545 --> 00:15.248
- Oh, they're gonna have a
weekend rendezvous, look out.

00:15.348 --> 00:17.484
[laughter]

00:20.487 --> 00:23.223
<i>- One day, a friend of mine,</i>
<i>an Englishman,</i>

00:23.323 --> 00:26.026
who lives in Los Angeles,
who was in the world of film,

00:26.092 --> 00:29.362
he called me and told me that
he had two friends in town,

00:29.429 --> 00:30.730
<i>a filmmaker who was making</i>

00:30.830 --> 00:32.766
<i>an important indie film</i>
<i>in London,</i>

00:32.866 --> 00:34.267
<i>and his girlfriend.</i>

00:34.367 --> 00:36.369
I learned that
this is Simon Monjack.

00:36.436 --> 00:38.772
He said his grandfather
founded British Steel,

00:38.872 --> 00:41.274
something like that,
and he's worth $1 billion.

00:41.374 --> 00:43.243
Since I'd never met
a billionaire before,

00:43.343 --> 00:46.880
and I'm a very curious person,
I decided to host a dinner.

00:46.946 --> 00:48.081
[glasses clink]

00:48.181 --> 00:49.582
<i>So Simon kind of held forth</i>

00:49.682 --> 00:51.518
<i>and he kind of</i>
<i>controlled the table.</i>

00:51.584 --> 00:54.587
<i>And he told us a lot of things</i>
<i>about himself that night.</i>

00:54.687 --> 00:58.124
<i>He said that he was the</i>
<i>largest collector of Vermeer,</i>

00:58.224 --> 00:59.859
<i>the great Dutch painter.</i>

00:59.926 --> 01:02.062
<i>He had more Vermeers</i>
<i>than anyone else in the world.</i>

01:02.128 --> 01:05.098
<i>He had dated Elle Macpherson</i>
<i>and Madonna.</i>

01:05.198 --> 01:07.634
<i>He said that he had been dying</i>
<i>from terminal brain cancer</i>

01:07.734 --> 01:10.603
<i>and that he had bought</i>
<i>an experimental treatment</i>

01:10.703 --> 01:13.139
<i>derived from</i>
<i>the fins of sharks</i>

01:13.239 --> 01:14.908
<i>and that it</i>
<i>had saved his life.</i>

01:14.974 --> 01:17.410
<i>He said that he had</i>
<i>a collection of Ferraris,</i>

01:17.477 --> 01:19.079
<i>17 in all.</i>

01:19.145 --> 01:20.947
<i>You know, we laughed</i>
<i>and we had a good time,</i>

01:21.047 --> 01:23.116
and, you know, I wondered
if he'd ever finance

01:23.216 --> 01:24.717
one of the movies
I wanted to make,

01:24.784 --> 01:26.052
<i>and that was it.</i>

01:26.119 --> 01:27.987
The only hint
that anything was askew

01:28.088 --> 01:30.457
<i>was that Simon</i>
<i>had told me his movie</i>

01:30.557 --> 01:32.659
<i>was getting the best reviews</i>

01:32.759 --> 01:35.261
<i>in the history of independent</i>
<i>film in England.</i>

01:35.328 --> 01:38.298
My friend, in London,
went to see the movie,

01:38.398 --> 01:39.799
and he came back and he said,

01:39.899 --> 01:41.468
"This is--
it's pretty terrible."

01:41.568 --> 01:43.403
- In this generation of lust,

01:43.470 --> 01:47.006
I never [...] found you, Lucy.

01:47.107 --> 01:49.676
No, I can't hear you, Lucy.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.144
[tires screeching]

01:51.244 --> 01:53.246
[screaming]

01:53.313 --> 01:54.948
- So that was kind of shocking.

01:56.249 --> 02:01.421
Time goes by, I get an email
from his girlfriend.

02:01.488 --> 02:05.492
And I find out that
every single word

02:05.592 --> 02:07.260
out of his mouth
was a lie.

02:07.327 --> 02:11.698
<i>One of the ways that Simon</i>
<i>legitimized those lies</i>

02:11.798 --> 02:15.335
<i>was by bringing a lovely girl</i>
<i>into the equation.</i>

02:15.435 --> 02:17.003
That was the cloak.

02:17.103 --> 02:19.706
And it was perfect because
she believed the lies too.

02:19.806 --> 02:23.843
<i>So he lived off this girl</i>
<i>that had worked her heart out</i>

02:23.943 --> 02:25.678
<i>for every penny she had.</i>

02:25.778 --> 02:28.148
<i>And when her money ran out,</i>
<i>he was gone.</i>

02:28.214 --> 02:32.785
And very quickly, he became
engaged to one of her friends.

02:32.852 --> 02:37.323
<i>I can't stress enough</i>
<i>how convincing this man was.</i>

02:39.792 --> 02:42.862
<i>["Die Young"</i>
<i>by Sylvan Esso playing]</i>

02:42.962 --> 02:48.134
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:48.201 --> 02:53.973
<i>- ♪ I had it all planned out</i>
<i>before you met me ♪</i>

02:54.040 --> 02:58.678
<i>♪ Was gonna leave early</i>
<i>and so swiftly ♪</i>

02:58.745 --> 03:03.149
<i>♪ Maybe in a fire</i>
<i>or crash off a ravine ♪</i>

03:03.216 --> 03:08.555
<i>♪ People would weep,</i>
<i>how tragic, so early ♪</i>

03:08.655 --> 03:13.026
<i>♪ I was gonna die young ♪</i>

03:13.092 --> 03:18.164
<i>♪ Now I gotta wait</i>
<i>for you honey ♪</i>

03:18.231 --> 03:22.068
<i>♪ I was gonna die young ♪</i>

03:25.405 --> 03:28.508
[thunder rumbles]

03:33.680 --> 03:35.848
<i>- I want to talk now</i>
<i>about Brittany Murphy,</i>

03:35.915 --> 03:37.417
<i>her controversial husband.</i>

03:37.517 --> 03:40.220
The unemployed British
screenwriter Simon Monjack

03:40.286 --> 03:42.288
<i>is being portrayed</i>
<i>as the villain,</i>

03:42.388 --> 03:45.124
<i>the drunken bully living off</i>
<i>a woman that he married</i>

03:45.225 --> 03:47.727
<i>because his visa had expired.</i>

03:47.794 --> 03:49.395
<i>- I don't think</i>
<i>Simon has recovered</i>

03:49.462 --> 03:51.531
<i>from the bad publicity.</i>
<i>He was like a Svengali.</i>

03:51.598 --> 03:54.200
- People don't die at home
with the husband present

03:54.267 --> 03:56.102
of pneumonia, of anemia.

03:56.202 --> 03:58.071
<i>- "Every story</i>
<i>needs a villain,"</i>

03:58.137 --> 04:01.708
<i>Monjack said after his wife's</i>
<i>tragic death, concluding,</i>

04:01.774 --> 04:04.444
<i>"And everyone decided</i>
<i>it is me."</i>

04:04.544 --> 04:06.546
<i>And on that point,</i>
<i>ladies and gentlemen,</i>

04:06.613 --> 04:09.549
<i>I agree with him.</i>

04:12.919 --> 04:15.655
<i>- I'm Linda Monjack,</i>
<i>and I am</i>

04:15.755 --> 04:18.391
Simon Monjack's mother.

04:18.458 --> 04:21.894
- And I'm James Monjack,
Simon's brother.

04:21.961 --> 04:23.296
<i>- As he was growing up,</i>

04:23.396 --> 04:25.632
<i>Simon was</i>
<i>the most incredible guy.</i>

04:25.732 --> 04:29.102
<i>He had an IQ off the scale.</i>

04:29.168 --> 04:33.506
<i>He was able to charm anyone,</i>
<i>old ladies, mothers.</i>

04:33.606 --> 04:35.908
<i>He would turn</i>
<i>his charm on anyone.</i>

04:35.975 --> 04:39.312
- From early childhood,
Simon had that ability

04:39.412 --> 04:41.314
to manipulate the environment

04:41.414 --> 04:44.017
to get what he wanted
out of it.

04:44.117 --> 04:47.654
<i>- Simon was 16</i>
<i>when his father died.</i>

04:47.754 --> 04:50.189
<i>It was a terrible,</i>
<i>terrible shock.</i>

04:50.290 --> 04:51.858
<i>He never was the same again.</i>

04:51.958 --> 04:54.627
<i>He was still witty</i>
<i>and full of life and funny,</i>

04:54.694 --> 04:56.529
but something died in him.

04:56.629 --> 05:01.501
And I think he became
more and more...

05:01.601 --> 05:04.170
unreal.

05:04.270 --> 05:07.173
<i>He lived in the now.</i>
<i>The now is important.</i>

05:07.273 --> 05:09.309
<i>The now meant</i>
<i>everything to him.</i>

05:09.375 --> 05:11.678
<i>In a minute,</i>
<i>that's not the now.</i>

05:11.778 --> 05:13.179
<i>The next moment happened,</i>

05:13.279 --> 05:15.715
<i>and there's a new moment</i>
<i>to experience.</i>

05:16.849 --> 05:20.453
<i>But he did fall in</i>
<i>and out of love very easily.</i>

05:20.520 --> 05:22.989
<i>He was in a very good place</i>
<i>when he met Brittany.</i>

05:23.056 --> 05:24.357
<i>They were very much in love.</i>

05:24.457 --> 05:25.992
<i>When you saw them together,</i>

05:26.059 --> 05:28.194
<i>they literally fell</i>
<i>into each other's eyes.</i>

05:28.294 --> 05:30.697
<i>I mean, literally drowned</i>
<i>in each other.</i>

05:30.797 --> 05:33.833
<i>The one conversation</i>
<i>that I remember with her</i>

05:33.900 --> 05:36.536
<i>was just before she died,</i>
<i>and I said,</i>

05:36.636 --> 05:39.372
"Oh, Brittany, Simon tells me
you're not feeling well.

05:39.472 --> 05:40.740
What's the matter?"

05:40.840 --> 05:42.375
She said,
"I'm having trouble breathing.

05:42.475 --> 05:44.677
If I go up the stairs,"
she was like,

05:44.744 --> 05:46.546
"By the time I get
to the top of the stairs,

05:46.646 --> 05:47.880
I can't breathe."

05:47.980 --> 05:49.649
She said,
"Do you think I'm dying?"

05:49.716 --> 05:51.551
So I said, "No, of course
you're not dying, you're fine.

05:51.651 --> 05:54.153
<i>But you need to go</i>
<i>to the doctor."</i>

05:54.220 --> 05:56.889
[siren wails]

05:56.989 --> 06:00.526
<i>I didn't speak to them again</i>
<i>until Simon phoned me</i>

06:00.593 --> 06:02.729
<i>on that terrible day.</i>

06:02.829 --> 06:04.931
<i>He was totally devastated,</i>

06:05.031 --> 06:08.401
<i>and he cried for about</i>
<i>two hours on the phone.</i>

06:08.501 --> 06:10.203
<i>He just could not get</i>
<i>his head around it.</i>

06:10.269 --> 06:13.539
He kept saying, "She's dead.
How can--she can't be.

06:13.606 --> 06:14.741
How? How?"

06:14.841 --> 06:17.744
<i>[somber music]</i>

06:17.844 --> 06:22.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:22.682 --> 06:25.351
<i>He was in shock for months.</i>

06:26.853 --> 06:29.021
<i>Nobody could get</i>
<i>through to him.</i>

06:29.088 --> 06:31.090
<i>He's too frightened</i>
<i>of the paparazzi,</i>

06:31.190 --> 06:35.528
and he was getting
increasingly ill.

06:35.595 --> 06:39.699
<i>And you could see it in</i>
<i>his face, his hair was wild.</i>

06:39.766 --> 06:42.602
<i>I phoned him, and I couldn't</i>
<i>get him for a couple of hours.</i>

06:42.702 --> 06:45.438
And I finally got hold of him,
and he said, "I'm alive.

06:45.538 --> 06:48.074
I'm alive.
I went sleep and I'm alive."

06:48.141 --> 06:50.710
Which I couldn't get
my head around.

06:50.777 --> 06:54.380
I didn't know why
he would say such a thing.

06:54.447 --> 06:56.082
<i>He was confused.</i>

06:56.149 --> 07:01.120
<i>So I think he felt</i>
<i>let down by everyone.</i>

07:05.324 --> 07:07.160
[birds cawing]

07:07.260 --> 07:11.330
<i>[clock ticking, bell chimes]</i>

07:11.431 --> 07:15.001
<i>- In May, I had</i>
<i>taken a trip to Hawaii</i>

07:15.101 --> 07:17.437
<i>with, like, a significant</i>
<i>other at the time.</i>

07:17.503 --> 07:19.272
Simon called me a lot.

07:19.338 --> 07:21.941
And I didn't answer a lot
because I was,

07:22.008 --> 07:23.810
like,
"No, I'm on vacation."

07:23.910 --> 07:25.311
<i>Some of his messages,</i>

07:25.411 --> 07:28.080
<i>you could sense</i>
<i>this growing frustration</i>

07:28.147 --> 07:30.650
<i>that I wasn't there for him.</i>

07:30.750 --> 07:33.453
<i>I certainly never viewed</i>
<i>my friendship with Simon</i>

07:33.519 --> 07:35.154
<i>as anything romantic.</i>

07:35.254 --> 07:38.458
And I don't think he did.
I mean, I have a wife.

07:38.524 --> 07:39.992
I don't even look
at men that way,

07:40.092 --> 07:42.428
so it definitely
wasn't something,

07:42.495 --> 07:47.600
<i>but it did cross my mind</i>
<i>just because you never know.</i>

07:47.667 --> 07:51.671
That probably was hard
for him at the time.

07:51.771 --> 07:54.006
I'll never know
because it was

07:54.106 --> 07:57.310
right after I got home
from that trip that he died.

07:57.376 --> 07:58.878
<i>[helicopter blades whipping]</i>

07:58.978 --> 08:01.347
[indistinct radio chatter]

08:01.447 --> 08:03.716
[siren wails]

08:03.816 --> 08:06.953
[indistinct chatter]

08:10.223 --> 08:13.226
- Everybody ready?
- Yes, sir.

08:13.326 --> 08:19.298
- This evening, Mr. Monjack
was found unresponsive.

08:19.365 --> 08:21.534
Paramedics responded
to the house.

08:21.634 --> 08:25.304
He was pronounced
at 2145 hours.

08:25.371 --> 08:27.306
His death
is under investigation

08:27.373 --> 08:30.009
by the Los Angeles County
Department of Coroner

08:30.076 --> 08:33.813
with the assistance of LAPD.

08:33.880 --> 08:35.748
<i>I got notified</i>
<i>of Simon's death,</i>

08:35.848 --> 08:40.052
and then it's like,
"Are you kidding me?"

08:40.152 --> 08:41.754
<i>- I get a call in the night.</i>

08:41.854 --> 08:44.557
Sharon's screaming,
"Please, please come here.

08:44.657 --> 08:46.993
"Please come here.
It's happening all over again.

08:47.059 --> 08:50.429
I'm living Brittany
all over again."

08:50.530 --> 08:54.166
<i>So I get in the car,</i>
<i>head up to the house,</i>

08:54.233 --> 08:58.437
<i>and when I get up there,</i>
<i>there is media everywhere.</i>

08:58.538 --> 08:59.906
<i>I couldn't get to the gate,</i>

09:00.006 --> 09:02.542
<i>much less</i>
<i>get through the gate.</i>

09:06.946 --> 09:08.581
- That's a day I won't forget.

09:08.681 --> 09:12.752
Simon came out,
he was sweating.

09:12.852 --> 09:14.720
<i>And he's got a cigar</i>
<i>in one hand,</i>

09:14.787 --> 09:17.924
<i>a cognac in the other hand,</i>
<i>but he would be talking to me</i>

09:18.024 --> 09:20.226
<i>and he would drift off</i>
<i>to sleep.</i>

09:20.293 --> 09:21.861
<i>And then he would just</i>
<i>open his eyes</i>

09:21.928 --> 09:23.396
<i>and come back</i>
<i>into the conversation</i>

09:23.462 --> 09:24.797
<i>like he was there</i>
<i>the whole time.</i>

09:24.897 --> 09:26.899
<i>And when I think</i>
<i>back about it,</i>

09:26.966 --> 09:28.734
he's dying in front of me,

09:28.801 --> 09:31.137
and I don't know
he's dying in front of me.

09:31.237 --> 09:34.607
- Here's a copy of
Simon Monjack's report.

09:34.707 --> 09:36.208
Cause of death is listed as

09:36.275 --> 09:39.478
<i>community acquired acute</i>
<i>bronchial pneumonia.</i>

09:39.579 --> 09:41.747
<i>The toxicology study</i>

09:41.814 --> 09:45.284
<i>showed the presence</i>
<i>of multiple medications.</i>

09:45.384 --> 09:48.454
<i>The media, they said,</i>
<i>"Isn't that strange?</i>

09:48.554 --> 09:51.157
<i>Both died from the same</i>
<i>cause of death."</i>

09:51.257 --> 09:54.226
And it'd be like, "Yeah,
we don't get a lot of those."

09:54.293 --> 09:57.964
- Just five months
after Brittany passed away,

09:58.064 --> 10:03.102
Simon, her husband, passed away
in the same bathroom

10:03.169 --> 10:08.341
in the same mansion
for almost identical reasons.

10:08.441 --> 10:12.612
- A small, tiny, petite woman
and a very large man,

10:12.678 --> 10:15.581
they die of the same thing
in the same house.

10:15.648 --> 10:19.185
- People start thinking
there's more behind this,

10:19.285 --> 10:21.320
there's something else.

10:21.420 --> 10:24.323
<i>[dark music]</i>

10:24.423 --> 10:26.926
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:26.993 --> 10:30.096
[wind whistling]

10:33.099 --> 10:37.103
<i>- After Simon died,</i>
<i>it was like, "What happened?"</i>

10:37.169 --> 10:38.671
<i>You know?</i>

10:38.771 --> 10:41.507
<i>I think the initial</i>
<i>thought was like something</i>

10:41.607 --> 10:44.710
is causing this
in the house.

10:44.810 --> 10:47.880
<i>- I've pleaded with Simon</i>
<i>to go to the hospital.</i>

10:47.980 --> 10:49.515
<i>He looked terrible.</i>

10:49.615 --> 10:53.786
My husband was very worried
because he's a builder,

10:53.853 --> 10:57.323
and he thought
it was to do with the mold.

10:57.390 --> 11:00.192
<i>- To me, it was obvious</i>
<i>when I went to the house,</i>

11:00.292 --> 11:02.862
<i>in this gorgeous</i>
<i>picture window.</i>

11:02.962 --> 11:05.031
I'm looking around
the frame of that window

11:05.131 --> 11:10.002
and you visibly see mold
on the side,

11:10.069 --> 11:12.171
<i>across the top,</i>
<i>across the bottom,</i>

11:12.238 --> 11:15.541
<i>and I look over to the French</i>
<i>doors and there's mold there.</i>

11:15.641 --> 11:17.877
<i>I don't think there's</i>
<i>any other explanation</i>

11:17.977 --> 11:19.578
<i>for their death.</i>

11:19.679 --> 11:22.214
<i>- All of the symptoms,</i>
<i>disorientation,</i>

11:22.314 --> 11:24.750
<i>feeling sick,</i>
<i>dreadful headaches,</i>

11:24.850 --> 11:30.156
all these things come from
inhaling spores from mold.

11:30.222 --> 11:32.391
<i>- Sharon Murphy</i>
<i>claims she discovered</i>

11:32.491 --> 11:35.227
<i>deadly mold hiding</i>
<i>in the walls of their mansion.</i>

11:35.327 --> 11:38.698
<i>Just look at what we found</i>
<i>at Brittany's home today.</i>

11:38.764 --> 11:42.068
- I know that there
were rumors that toxic mold

11:42.168 --> 11:44.403
may have played a role
in Brittany's death

11:44.503 --> 11:46.906
and possibly the death
of her husband.

11:47.006 --> 11:49.608
But on my autopsy,

11:49.709 --> 11:53.045
<i>I didn't see any evidence</i>
<i>of mold in her lungs</i>

11:53.112 --> 11:56.182
<i>or any other organs because</i>
<i>you can see the hyphae,</i>

11:56.248 --> 12:00.086
<i>which are little strands of</i>
<i>mold or the fruiting bodies.</i>

12:00.186 --> 12:03.723
<i>- I told Sharon I would get</i>
<i>somebody from County Health</i>

12:03.789 --> 12:06.192
<i>to come up</i>
<i>and they'd check the house.</i>

12:06.258 --> 12:08.561
<i>And then I got a call</i>
<i>from her attorney</i>

12:08.627 --> 12:11.030
who said Sharon doesn't want
to give any access,

12:11.097 --> 12:13.532
and she's selling
the house anyway.

12:13.599 --> 12:15.901
Just stay away.

12:15.968 --> 12:19.605
<i>- New shocking allegations</i>
<i>coming from her father,</i>

12:19.705 --> 12:21.474
<i>who says she was poisoned.</i>

12:21.574 --> 12:24.543
<i>And Murphy's father, Angelo</i>
<i>Bertolotti, joining us now.</i>

12:24.610 --> 12:26.979
Angelo, do you
suspect somebody?

12:27.079 --> 12:31.984
- Yeah, I do really, but I'd
rather not speak about that.

12:32.084 --> 12:34.086
I feel she was poisoned.

12:34.153 --> 12:36.288
<i>There's no question</i>
<i>about that.</i>

12:36.388 --> 12:39.125
And I feel she was murdered.

12:39.225 --> 12:41.794
<i>- Once the two of them</i>
<i>had died of the same cause,</i>

12:41.894 --> 12:44.964
<i>Brittany's dad</i>
<i>reached out to me.</i>

12:45.064 --> 12:49.802
He was sure that
someone had done it.

12:49.902 --> 12:53.272
<i>- Angelo Bertolotti</i>
<i>lived down in Florida</i>

12:53.339 --> 12:56.308
and ran a string
of nightclubs.

12:56.408 --> 13:01.313
- Sharon, Brittany's mom,
really does not like Angelo.

13:01.413 --> 13:03.315
She said that he only
came around

13:03.415 --> 13:04.817
when she started making money.

13:04.917 --> 13:06.685
- He says, "I was involved
with the mob.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.988
I wasn't very involved
in my marriage."

13:09.088 --> 13:12.825
<i>- Angelo was actually banned</i>
<i>from ever seeing his daughter</i>

13:12.925 --> 13:17.163
at the gravesite multiple times
until he was able to prove

13:17.263 --> 13:20.533
he was the biological father
of Brittany Murphy.

13:20.633 --> 13:21.967
That's horrible.

13:22.034 --> 13:24.003
- Take two.

13:24.103 --> 13:25.871
<i>- I'm Wendy Abrahamson,</i>

13:25.971 --> 13:28.040
and I was a fan of Brittany

13:28.140 --> 13:31.877
and the best friend
of her father Angelo.

13:31.977 --> 13:36.348
<i>So her dad, he needed help</i>
<i>to find her grave,</i>

13:36.448 --> 13:40.052
<i>and so some of the fans said,</i>
<i>"Oh, we're gonna help."</i>

13:40.152 --> 13:41.821
We just became really close.

13:41.887 --> 13:45.891
Of course, that common
denominator of Brittany

13:45.991 --> 13:50.062
<i>started it and then we were</i>
<i>just best friends.</i>

13:50.162 --> 13:52.331
And of course, he thought
it was really strange

13:52.398 --> 13:58.337
that the mother, his ex-wife,
was perfectly fine.

13:58.404 --> 14:01.640
And that the married couple,
much younger than her,

14:01.707 --> 14:03.075
were both dead.

14:03.175 --> 14:06.812
These are things
that nobody has seen.

14:06.879 --> 14:09.181
We went, of course,
to the coroner's office

14:09.248 --> 14:13.986
to obtain the hair samples
and have those tested.

14:14.053 --> 14:17.556
<i>- Ed Winter says his office</i>
<i>did forward toxicology samples</i>

14:17.656 --> 14:20.559
<i>to a private lab hired</i>
<i>by the late actress's father.</i>

14:20.659 --> 14:23.195
<i>The private analysis</i>
<i>states Brittany Murphy</i>

14:23.262 --> 14:26.665
<i>had high concentrations of ten</i>
<i>heavy metals in her system</i>

14:26.732 --> 14:29.168
<i>and may have been</i>
<i>intentionally poison.</i>

14:29.235 --> 14:34.406
- I received a call, an email
from Angelo Bertolotti.

14:34.506 --> 14:39.245
I can understand him asking,

14:39.345 --> 14:43.282
"What are you telling me,
my 32-year-old daughter,

14:43.382 --> 14:47.620
she just died like that
from pneumonia and anemia?"

14:47.720 --> 14:51.190
<i>He then said he had gotten</i>
<i>hold of a toxicology report</i>

14:51.257 --> 14:52.758
<i>on a sample of hair,</i>

14:52.858 --> 14:56.061
<i>and it showed heavy levels</i>
<i>of heavy metals.</i>

14:56.128 --> 14:59.031
I've had cases like that,
fascinating cases,

14:59.098 --> 15:02.201
one with a woman
who was repeatedly poisoning

15:02.268 --> 15:04.136
her husband with thallium.

15:04.236 --> 15:06.305
I'm not unfamiliar with that.

15:06.405 --> 15:08.107
<i>- Heavy metals</i>
<i>are commonly found</i>

15:08.207 --> 15:09.608
<i>in rat and insect killers.</i>

15:09.708 --> 15:11.110
<i>They can cause the symptoms</i>

15:11.210 --> 15:13.379
<i>Murphy experienced</i>
<i>before her death.</i>

15:13.445 --> 15:17.149
<i>- I absolutely, positively</i>
<i>thinks she was poisoned, yes.</i>

15:17.249 --> 15:20.052
I'm calling for her
to be exhumed.

15:20.119 --> 15:23.322
- You know, Angelo was
in the press quite a bit.

15:23.422 --> 15:25.157
And they were
putting stuff out there,

15:25.257 --> 15:26.825
<i>like she poisoned them.</i>

15:26.926 --> 15:28.794
<i>She's responsible</i>
<i>for their deaths.</i>

15:28.894 --> 15:30.596
<i>So what happens?</i>

15:30.663 --> 15:32.831
<i>You got a grieving mom who now</i>
<i>becomes a murder suspect.</i>

15:32.932 --> 15:34.934
<i>That's ridiculous.</i>
<i>I mean, it's crazy.</i>

15:35.000 --> 15:38.437
<i>- It was just magazine covers</i>
<i>and salacious headlines,</i>

15:38.504 --> 15:40.172
and it became this circus.

15:40.272 --> 15:43.842
So that's when the conspiracy
theories go into overdrive.

15:43.943 --> 15:45.978
- Like, maybe her mother
could have had something

15:46.078 --> 15:48.314
to do with it,
just speculation.

15:48.414 --> 15:51.951
- It was a plan from
the beginning for both of them

15:52.017 --> 15:54.453
to take her money
after she died.

15:54.520 --> 15:58.290
And the mom
got the last laugh.

15:58.357 --> 16:00.859
- I would never put two
and two together,

16:00.960 --> 16:04.163
but these days and age,
mothers, you know,

16:04.263 --> 16:08.100
they take out their kids
all the time.

16:08.167 --> 16:13.005
<i>- Brittany and Sharon were as</i>
<i>close as two people could be.</i>

16:13.105 --> 16:17.343
Maybe Sharon
made some mistakes.

16:18.277 --> 16:22.481
But I know that she loved
that girl wildly.

16:23.449 --> 16:26.018
<i>- Never for a minute</i>
<i>did I ever believe</i>

16:26.118 --> 16:28.954
<i>that Sharon Murphy</i>
<i>was responsible</i>

16:29.021 --> 16:30.656
<i>for those</i>
<i>two young people dying.</i>

16:30.723 --> 16:33.192
I would never believe it.

16:33.292 --> 16:35.861
Not for a millisecond.

16:35.961 --> 16:40.966
- Initially, when I was given
this private laboratory report,

16:41.033 --> 16:42.801
I said, "Oh, my God.
What is this?"

16:42.868 --> 16:46.672
And then I looked
carefully and saw

16:46.739 --> 16:49.041
that this was not
a case of poisoning.

16:49.141 --> 16:52.711
The heavy metals were found
in the hair, not in the roots.

16:52.811 --> 16:57.416
Heavy metals take a while
to be absorbed from the blood.

16:57.516 --> 16:59.685
<i>In order to be in the hair,</i>

16:59.752 --> 17:01.854
<i>they got to be picked up</i>
<i>by the hair root,</i>

17:01.920 --> 17:03.856
<i>and then they got to grow out.</i>

17:03.922 --> 17:08.560
These metals had to have come
from hairsprays, hair dyes,

17:08.660 --> 17:10.329
and things of that nature.

17:10.396 --> 17:12.031
They are not
in her bloodstream.

17:12.097 --> 17:13.532
They are in her hair.

17:13.599 --> 17:18.103
Did she die because
someone poisoned her?

17:18.203 --> 17:19.705
No.

17:19.772 --> 17:22.441
<i>- There were elevated levels</i>
<i>of things like aluminum</i>

17:22.541 --> 17:24.843
or one or two other things,
but it's hair dye.

17:24.910 --> 17:26.578
That's what does it.

17:26.678 --> 17:29.615
<i>And Brittany has dyed her hair</i>
<i>many different times.</i>

17:29.715 --> 17:33.585
And I didn't see any evidence
of any type of poison.

17:33.685 --> 17:35.587
<i>- There is no question</i>
<i>in my mind</i>

17:35.687 --> 17:37.256
<i>about the cause of death.</i>

17:37.356 --> 17:40.092
So this is
a 32-year-old woman.

17:40.192 --> 17:44.263
I don't know the bankroll
of her and her husband,

17:44.363 --> 17:46.598
<i>but I assume</i>
<i>that they had money.</i>

17:46.698 --> 17:50.436
<i>And yet they lived as if</i>
<i>they were peasants in squalor.</i>

17:50.536 --> 17:53.405
<i>To develop an anemia</i>
<i>of this nature,</i>

17:53.472 --> 17:55.140
<i>she was not eating.</i>

17:55.240 --> 17:57.409
<i>How did all of this develop?</i>

17:57.476 --> 17:59.278
<i>That's the fascinating</i>
<i>question.</i>

17:59.378 --> 18:01.747
This is where you got to bring
in the forensic psychiatrist

18:01.814 --> 18:05.551
and see if he can dig up
enough information about her

18:05.617 --> 18:07.653
<i>and her husband Simon Monjack</i>

18:07.753 --> 18:10.756
<i>to try to answer</i>
<i>that question.</i>

18:17.596 --> 18:19.798
- That was during a little dip
she was having

18:19.898 --> 18:21.266
that he came along.

18:21.333 --> 18:25.838
And I think that's
where her judgment

18:25.938 --> 18:29.074
was muddled and desperate,

18:29.141 --> 18:31.610
and she became prey to things

18:31.677 --> 18:34.012
that she thought
would help her.

18:36.014 --> 18:39.485
<i>[tense music]</i>

18:39.585 --> 18:42.921
<i>- I feel like what brought</i>
<i>Brittany Murphy's career down</i>

18:42.988 --> 18:47.292
<i>is a perfect storm of getting</i>
<i>cast in the wrong movies</i>

18:47.359 --> 18:49.128
<i>and her personal life.</i>

18:49.194 --> 18:53.799
Mid 2000s, the biggest rumors
that I was hearing

18:53.866 --> 18:56.301
and not reporting
were about drugs.

18:56.368 --> 18:57.669
- Do we read them?

18:57.769 --> 19:00.839
No, we wait.
Okay.

19:00.939 --> 19:02.674
<i>- I remember her</i>
<i>as a presenter</i>

19:02.774 --> 19:05.444
at the 2003
Independent Spirit Awards,

19:05.511 --> 19:07.546
where her assignment
was to read the names

19:07.646 --> 19:08.847
of five nominees,

19:08.947 --> 19:10.849
open an envelope,
and read the winner.

19:10.949 --> 19:13.152
She kept trying to read
every nominee as the winner.

19:13.218 --> 19:15.187
<i>And when she arrived</i>
<i>triumphantly</i>

19:15.287 --> 19:16.889
<i>at the real winner,</i>

19:16.989 --> 19:19.858
<i>she inspired no confidence</i>
<i>that she had it right.</i>

19:19.958 --> 19:25.030
- America, just one moment,
please.

19:25.130 --> 19:26.532
audience: No!

19:26.632 --> 19:28.233
For crying out stinking loud,

19:28.333 --> 19:30.235
please tell me
when you're going to drop it.

19:30.335 --> 19:31.970
Okay.
And the winner is...

19:32.037 --> 19:34.072
audience: No!

19:36.642 --> 19:40.245
- Brittany Murphy, around
the beginning of my career,

19:40.345 --> 19:45.317
was talked about a lot.

19:45.384 --> 19:47.386
<i>I first started hearing rumors</i>

19:47.486 --> 19:50.522
<i>shortly after her split</i>
<i>from Ashton Kutcher,</i>

19:50.589 --> 19:53.725
<i>rumors about her just being</i>
<i>impossible to deal with,</i>

19:53.825 --> 19:58.063
<i>whereas Ashton was</i>
<i>the golden boy of Hollywood.</i>

19:58.163 --> 20:02.901
Ultimately, you can only
keep things quiet for so long.

20:03.001 --> 20:05.370
When it starts
to get out there,

20:05.437 --> 20:09.575
<i>then you start to develop</i>
<i>a reputation.</i>

20:09.675 --> 20:13.178
- Perez Hilton didn't get
to be Perez Hilton

20:13.245 --> 20:15.914
by writing nice stories
about celebrities.

20:16.014 --> 20:18.684
He was writing doodles
on their photos.

20:18.750 --> 20:20.619
<i>Brittany Murphy,</i>
<i>"Is she pill popping?"</i>

20:20.719 --> 20:22.754
<i>"Is she anorexic?"</i>
<i>"Is she bulimic?"</i>

20:22.854 --> 20:27.426
- I remember she called me
crying and said,

20:27.526 --> 20:29.094
"Can you call my manager?"

20:29.194 --> 20:32.864
Who was a very, very,
very big manager at the time.

20:32.931 --> 20:34.800
"He thinks I'm on drugs."

20:34.900 --> 20:38.604
<i>I know that hurt her deeply.</i>

20:38.704 --> 20:40.639
<i>- You were kind of nasty</i>
<i>at times.</i>

20:40.739 --> 20:42.107
- I was more than nasty.

20:42.207 --> 20:45.277
I--I didn't even view
Brittany Murphy

20:45.377 --> 20:49.581
or any of the celebrities
that I covered as real people.

20:49.648 --> 20:51.483
They were characters to me.

20:51.583 --> 20:52.818
It was almost like a way

20:52.918 --> 20:56.588
to disassociate myself
from my actions,

20:56.655 --> 20:58.457
from what I was writing
and saying.

20:58.557 --> 21:00.425
"Oh, this isn't real,

21:00.492 --> 21:03.629
and also Perez
is a character."

21:03.729 --> 21:06.131
I would tell all these things
to myself

21:06.231 --> 21:09.268
to help me sleep at night.

21:10.402 --> 21:12.271
<i>If you're at a point</i>
<i>in your life</i>

21:12.337 --> 21:14.740
<i>where your career</i>
<i>is struggling,</i>

21:14.806 --> 21:18.577
<i>your personal life</i>
<i>is also struggling,</i>

21:18.644 --> 21:23.415
<i>you might be drawn</i>
<i>to the wrong people.</i>

21:23.482 --> 21:26.985
[indistinct chatter]

21:27.085 --> 21:28.587
- Hey, hey, hey!
Whoa!

21:28.654 --> 21:30.489
- Brittany, can we get
a fashion shot?

21:30.589 --> 21:31.990
<i>- She was an open vessel.</i>

21:32.090 --> 21:35.327
<i>If she trusted you,</i>
<i>she let you in.</i>

21:35.427 --> 21:38.430
<i>He saw her coming</i>
<i>a mile away.</i>

21:38.497 --> 21:41.366
<i>She was pure, trusting,</i>

21:41.466 --> 21:45.837
<i>loving, open,</i>
<i>and he saw her coming.</i>

21:45.937 --> 21:48.640
- And got it.
Mark.

21:48.707 --> 21:50.309
Great.
Thank you.

21:50.375 --> 21:52.144
- My name is Harley Pasternak.

21:52.210 --> 21:55.213
I am a celebrity fitness
and nutrition author.

21:55.314 --> 22:00.819
I trained Simon Monjack
a number of years ago.

22:02.187 --> 22:03.522
<i>First time I met Simon,</i>

22:03.622 --> 22:05.857
<i>he rolled up</i>
<i>in a vintage Ferrari,</i>

22:05.957 --> 22:08.393
<i>and he got out smoking</i>
<i>these fancy, I think,</i>

22:08.493 --> 22:10.629
<i>Cohiba cigars,</i>
<i>and his girlfriend</i>

22:10.696 --> 22:12.531
<i>had the biggest diamond ring</i>
<i>you've ever seen.</i>

22:12.631 --> 22:15.400
<i>They got engaged the night</i>
<i>before, and she was happy.</i>

22:15.500 --> 22:18.337
And then he said, "We're both
gonna work with you."

22:18.403 --> 22:21.873
And then his balance
started to run up a lot more,

22:21.973 --> 22:24.042
and I wouldn't let him
book new sessions.

22:24.142 --> 22:25.744
And then he called me
one day and he says,

22:25.844 --> 22:28.547
"Hey, I'm dating
Brittany Murphy now.

22:28.647 --> 22:31.350
"And I want to bring her in and
for us to work out together,

22:31.416 --> 22:33.385
and I'll pay you
what I owe you."

22:33.485 --> 22:35.354
And they showed up one day.

22:35.420 --> 22:38.724
Brittany was for sure under
the influence of something.

22:38.824 --> 22:40.025
Pills maybe.

22:40.092 --> 22:41.893
She was kind of slurring
her words.

22:41.993 --> 22:44.563
She was very sweet and--and--

22:44.663 --> 22:46.365
but kind of
all over the place.

22:46.431 --> 22:48.900
<i>And he said,</i>
<i>"Brittany's got a big project,</i>

22:49.000 --> 22:51.436
<i>and I want you to get her</i>
<i>ready for the role."</i>

22:51.536 --> 22:54.506
<i>"Okay, well, if I'm</i>
<i>gonna work with Brittany,</i>

22:54.573 --> 22:56.241
<i>I'll just deal</i>
<i>with her team."</i>

22:56.341 --> 22:58.043
And I remember reaching out
to her team and saying,

22:58.110 --> 22:59.845
"She fired all of us.

22:59.911 --> 23:03.181
"Simon is her agent, manager,
and lawyer and everything now.

23:03.248 --> 23:05.250
You have to go through Simon."

23:05.350 --> 23:06.852
And they said,
"We're concerned

23:06.918 --> 23:10.088
"because no one
can contact her directly.

23:10.188 --> 23:11.790
You can only
go through Simon."

23:11.890 --> 23:13.392
I don't even know
if she had a phone.

23:13.458 --> 23:15.594
Simon was the only one
who carried the phone.

23:18.864 --> 23:21.967
- She just seemed
like she was high.

23:22.067 --> 23:25.103
So I don't--I don't know.

23:25.203 --> 23:28.140
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

23:28.240 --> 23:30.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:30.976 --> 23:33.712
<i>- I would say</i>
<i>that Simon Monjack</i>

23:33.779 --> 23:36.815
accelerated the path
that Brittany Murphy

23:36.915 --> 23:39.951
was heading down by the time
that they got together.

23:40.051 --> 23:43.989
<i>- I couldn't believe that this</i>
<i>bottom-feeding sociopath</i>

23:44.089 --> 23:47.459
had actually worked his way
up the food chain

23:47.559 --> 23:50.562
to someone who was actually
a legitimate artist.

23:50.629 --> 23:52.998
<i>So the first thing I did</i>
<i>was I called her agency.</i>

23:53.098 --> 23:55.967
<i>I said, "You need to tell her</i>
<i>every word out of his mouth</i>

23:56.067 --> 23:59.304
<i>is a lie and that she's got</i>
<i>to get the hell out."</i>

23:59.404 --> 24:02.607
The word coming back
was her manager had tried

24:02.674 --> 24:04.643
and gotten fired
as a result,

24:04.743 --> 24:06.311
that there was
no talking to her.

24:06.411 --> 24:09.347
So I did something I never
imagined myself doing,

24:09.448 --> 24:11.483
I called
the "National Enquirer."

24:11.583 --> 24:13.018
<i>I called their tip line,</i>

24:13.118 --> 24:14.653
<i>and I said,</i>
<i>"I don't want money for this,</i>

24:14.753 --> 24:16.688
<i>because this guy</i>
<i>is dangerous."</i>

24:16.788 --> 24:21.526
<i>This big story comes out</i>
<i>about Simon and Brittany.</i>

24:21.626 --> 24:24.262
<i>A week later, Perez Hilton</i>
<i>came out with a headline</i>

24:24.329 --> 24:26.998
<i>that said</i>
<i>"The kook and the crook."</i>

24:27.098 --> 24:29.634
And I thought,
"Okay, my work is done here.

24:29.701 --> 24:31.503
I have gotten the word out."

24:31.603 --> 24:33.338
<i>- This is all starting</i>
<i>to come out.</i>

24:33.438 --> 24:37.008
<i>Her true friends know</i>
<i>that Simon's not good news.</i>

24:37.108 --> 24:39.778
There was this talk
of an intervention,

24:39.845 --> 24:43.815
and this intervention
took place at Brittany's house.

24:45.183 --> 24:47.219
<i>These friends</i>
<i>were showing Brittany</i>

24:47.319 --> 24:49.054
<i>and her mother documentation</i>

24:49.154 --> 24:52.023
<i>that, you know, Simon</i>
<i>had trouble with the law,</i>

24:52.123 --> 24:56.027
<i>that Simon had outstayed</i>
<i>his visa, which he had.</i>

24:56.127 --> 24:58.396
<i>Brittany and her mom said,</i>
<i>"No, we love Simon,</i>

24:58.497 --> 25:00.499
<i>and we believe Simon.</i>
<i>Sorry."</i>

25:00.565 --> 25:01.900
<i>And the intervention fails.</i>

25:02.000 --> 25:05.871
- Simon started building
a wall around her.

25:05.971 --> 25:08.006
<i>He took charge--</i>
<i>he took charge of finances,</i>

25:08.073 --> 25:09.407
<i>making investments.</i>

25:09.508 --> 25:11.176
<i>He was buying property.</i>

25:11.243 --> 25:15.213
<i>He was buying jewelry,</i>
<i>had a tiara made of diamonds</i>

25:15.313 --> 25:18.083
<i>that was a replica</i>
<i>of Audrey Hepburn's tiara</i>

25:18.183 --> 25:19.818
<i>in "Breakfast at Tiffany's."</i>

25:19.885 --> 25:21.386
<i>So they could have</i>

25:21.486 --> 25:23.588
<i>all these investments</i>
<i>to fall back on.</i>

25:23.688 --> 25:25.891
<i>- He was making</i>
<i>all of her decisions.</i>

25:25.991 --> 25:28.693
<i>He was clearly</i>
<i>getting her money.</i>

25:28.760 --> 25:32.397
<i>He started driving her</i>
<i>to work but waiting.</i>

25:32.497 --> 25:34.766
And every time
there was a break,

25:34.866 --> 25:37.502
she would leave
and go be in the car with him.

25:37.569 --> 25:39.571
And it got more
and more restrictive,

25:39.671 --> 25:41.706
and it got more and more
apparent to all of us

25:41.773 --> 25:43.375
that she wasn't hanging out

25:43.441 --> 25:46.444
or having lunch with us
or talking.

25:46.545 --> 25:49.247
- One day,
her numbers were changed.

25:49.347 --> 25:53.118
No one knew where she was,
couldn't find her.

25:53.218 --> 25:56.254
Disappeared.
Disappeared.

25:56.354 --> 25:59.457
Simon took her away.

25:59.558 --> 26:00.859
