<i>have the baby on U.S. soil."</i>

38:56.967 --> 39:01.505
<i>So Simon got me to New York,</i>
<i>and he was in Monaco.</i>

39:01.572 --> 39:03.708
<i>You know, he got my ticket</i>
<i>and everything,</i>

39:03.808 --> 39:06.010
<i>and I got there and I got up</i>
<i>into my little studio,</i>

39:06.077 --> 39:08.012
<i>and I called him</i>
<i>to tell him I was there.</i>

39:08.079 --> 39:10.548
And I said, "Simon,
I've made it, I'm here in--"

39:10.648 --> 39:13.150
Click, he hung up on me.

39:13.217 --> 39:16.887
And then trying to call him
back a million times

39:16.987 --> 39:19.690
<i>and realizing</i>
<i>he's just not picking up</i>

39:19.757 --> 39:21.926
<i>or something's happened to him</i>
<i>or something's wrong.</i>

39:22.026 --> 39:23.828
<i>And I started</i>
<i>looking for ways</i>

39:23.894 --> 39:25.563
to get in touch
with his mother.

39:25.663 --> 39:27.732
And I found his mother,
and she told me

39:27.832 --> 39:30.434
<i>that he didn't have</i>
<i>spinal cancer</i>

39:30.534 --> 39:33.504
<i>and that he had been</i>
<i>using her money for that.</i>

39:33.571 --> 39:35.573
<i>But she was furious with him.</i>

39:35.673 --> 39:37.742
<i>The owner of the villa</i>
<i>told me</i>

39:37.842 --> 39:41.746
<i>that he was already</i>
<i>with somebody else.</i>

39:41.846 --> 39:45.516
I thought about, um...

39:45.583 --> 39:47.918
killing myself

39:48.018 --> 39:50.554
because I didn't--

39:50.621 --> 39:54.125
Who does that?
I mean--

39:54.225 --> 40:00.564
And then the reason I didn't
is because of the baby.

40:00.631 --> 40:03.567
<i>[light music]</i>

40:03.634 --> 40:10.741
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:12.042 --> 40:14.278
<i>After not being in touch</i>
<i>for a long time,</i>

40:14.378 --> 40:16.781
<i>I worked in Paris</i>
<i>and lived outside Paris.</i>

40:16.881 --> 40:19.150
<i>And so I was on the train</i>
<i>coming home from work,</i>

40:19.250 --> 40:22.386
<i>reading a magazine, there was</i>
<i>a little picture that said,</i>

40:22.453 --> 40:23.954
<i>"Brittany Murphy</i>
<i>has married."</i>

40:24.054 --> 40:26.791
<i>And it was Simon.</i>
<i>He got in touch with me.</i>

40:26.891 --> 40:29.326
He offered, at that point,
to buy me a house,

40:29.427 --> 40:31.128
and we talked
for a little while,

40:31.228 --> 40:33.264
and that one ended with him

40:33.330 --> 40:35.466
threatening to come
and get my son.

40:35.566 --> 40:37.134
<i>So I was quiet.</i>

40:37.234 --> 40:39.270
<i>That, I believe,</i>
<i>was his intention</i>

40:39.336 --> 40:41.005
<i>was to try to keep me quiet</i>

40:41.105 --> 40:43.607
because the stakes
were a lot higher with him

40:43.674 --> 40:45.309
being married to Brittany.

40:45.409 --> 40:46.811
<i>He didn't need</i>
<i>anybody to know</i>

40:46.911 --> 40:50.648
<i>that I was out there</i>
<i>with his son.</i>

40:50.748 --> 40:53.317
<i>I know why Brittany</i>
<i>chose Simon.</i>

40:53.417 --> 40:56.821
He worked his spell on her.

40:56.921 --> 40:59.256
And she fell for it
like I did.

41:01.125 --> 41:03.994
- Everything is a lie?

41:04.094 --> 41:05.362
Everything is a lie.

41:05.463 --> 41:06.964
[static crackling]

41:07.031 --> 41:10.367
Every--every--everything--
everything is a lie.

41:10.468 --> 41:12.603
- Don't take it personally,
Mare.

41:12.670 --> 41:13.671
Mare Bear.

41:13.771 --> 41:15.372
- Don't touch me.

41:15.473 --> 41:21.212
- The man you fell in love
with is not real.

41:21.312 --> 41:24.181
<i>[somber music]</i>

41:24.281 --> 41:25.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:25.950 --> 41:29.019
<i>- So, you know, we did speak</i>
<i>to Elizabeth Ragsdale,</i>

41:29.119 --> 41:31.856
Elijah's mom.

41:31.956 --> 41:33.491
- Well, he never
acknowledged--

41:33.557 --> 41:38.496
you do know that he never
acknowledged his existence.

41:38.562 --> 41:40.164
<i>When you look at Elijah,</i>

41:40.231 --> 41:41.966
<i>you can see</i>
<i>there's a likeness,</i>

41:42.032 --> 41:45.169
<i>but what I'm saying</i>
<i>is that it's very difficult</i>

41:45.236 --> 41:48.072
to acknowledge something
that you don't know.

41:48.172 --> 41:50.708
- There's this story about
the shark fin treatments.

41:50.808 --> 41:52.510
Was there any truth
to any of that?

41:52.576 --> 41:56.847
- He was terribly fearful that
his father got cancer at 29.

41:56.914 --> 41:59.216
I certainly don't think
he went out to tell people,

41:59.316 --> 42:01.185
"I have cancer."
I think he believed it.

42:01.252 --> 42:04.021
- We heard that
Simon had actually

42:04.088 --> 42:06.490
swindled money off of you.

42:06.557 --> 42:09.326
- He never swindled money
from me.

42:09.393 --> 42:13.030
I gave him money,
copious amounts of money,

42:13.097 --> 42:17.067
but I just gave it willingly
and freely, probably foolishly.

42:17.167 --> 42:23.274
But nevertheless, he didn't--
he didn't cheat me.

42:32.116 --> 42:35.252
<i>[gentle music]</i>

42:35.352 --> 42:37.955
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:38.055 --> 42:39.423
<i>- Simon and Brittany</i>

42:39.523 --> 42:41.392
<i>were basically</i>
<i>locked up in that house.</i>

42:41.458 --> 42:43.427
<i>They did these really</i>
<i>weird photoshoots</i>

42:43.527 --> 42:44.895
<i>in the middle of the night</i>

42:44.962 --> 42:47.197
<i>where he would dress her</i>
<i>like a doll.</i>

42:47.264 --> 42:51.268
<i>He encouraged her to become</i>
<i>addicted to plastic surgery.</i>

42:51.368 --> 42:53.270
<i>He would tell her,</i>
<i>"Your teeth aren't right.</i>

42:53.370 --> 42:54.805
<i>"Your nose isn't right.</i>

42:54.905 --> 42:56.807
<i>We might need to do something</i>
<i>with your chin."</i>

42:56.907 --> 42:58.976
<i>And she became increasingly</i>
<i>insecure about her appearance,</i>

42:59.076 --> 43:02.580
<i>increasingly paranoid about</i>
<i>people being out to get her.</i>

43:03.981 --> 43:07.551
<i>Simon had the landlines</i>
<i>disconnected.</i>

43:07.618 --> 43:10.421
<i>So the only way you could</i>
<i>reach Sharon or Brittany</i>

43:10.487 --> 43:11.989
<i>was through Simon.</i>

43:12.089 --> 43:14.625
<i>Simon and Brittany</i>
<i>would stay up late nights</i>

43:14.725 --> 43:16.794
<i>and take downers</i>
<i>and then chug coffee</i>

43:16.894 --> 43:18.662
<i>and take uppers</i>
<i>to come back up.</i>

43:18.762 --> 43:20.965
<i>And, you know,</i>
<i>they rarely left the house.</i>

43:21.065 --> 43:23.934
<i>- I remember</i>
<i>I was at some show,</i>

43:24.001 --> 43:25.803
<i>like 40 minutes into it,</i>

43:25.903 --> 43:29.807
she shows up scooting
through the seats with Simon

43:29.907 --> 43:31.675
with, like, bleary eyes,

43:31.775 --> 43:34.645
and I just didn't
recognize her anymore.

43:34.745 --> 43:40.818
Brittany was
just cloudy and gone.

43:40.918 --> 43:46.190
<i>- It was alarming to see</i>
<i>how thin she had gotten.</i>

43:46.290 --> 43:48.125
<i>Emaciated.</i>

43:48.192 --> 43:51.128
<i>She was so frail.</i>

43:51.195 --> 43:54.431
<i>- When I saw Brittany Murphy</i>
<i>getting really thin,</i>

43:54.498 --> 43:57.201
I knew that he had
something to do with that.

43:57.301 --> 43:59.837
<i>He loved anorexic women.</i>

43:59.937 --> 44:04.508
He would look at me from behind
in my jeans and he would go,

44:04.608 --> 44:07.144
<i>"Do you really think</i>
<i>you need to wear those jeans?</i>

44:07.211 --> 44:11.348
Because, you know,
you look kind of--"

44:11.448 --> 44:12.883
<i>- He was everything.</i>

44:12.983 --> 44:15.185
<i>He was the agent.</i>
<i>He was the manager.</i>

44:15.285 --> 44:16.787
<i>He was the makeup artist.</i>

44:16.854 --> 44:18.856
<i>Nobody touched her.</i>
<i>Nobody got close to her.</i>

44:18.956 --> 44:20.024
<i>It was all him.</i>

44:20.124 --> 44:21.525
<i>When the offers are drying up</i>

44:21.625 --> 44:23.527
<i>because you got going</i>
<i>around town,</i>

44:23.627 --> 44:25.029
<i>"Don't deal with Brittany</i>

44:25.129 --> 44:26.697
<i>because her husband's</i>
<i>a lunatic,"</i>

44:26.797 --> 44:28.365
<i>he took what he could get.</i>

44:28.465 --> 44:30.367
- If you look at someone
who just a few years ago

44:30.467 --> 44:32.536
was in really iconic movies,

44:32.636 --> 44:34.405
I mean, "Eight Mile,"
"Clueless."

44:34.505 --> 44:36.907
These are movies that will
stand the test of time,

44:37.007 --> 44:39.877
<i>to then be in thrillers</i>
<i>and slashers</i>

44:39.977 --> 44:42.479
<i>that are going</i>
<i>straight to video,</i>

44:42.546 --> 44:45.049
<i>it looks like failure.</i>

44:45.149 --> 44:47.384
- Mark.

44:47.484 --> 44:48.719
<i>- I'm Trista Jordan.</i>

44:48.819 --> 44:50.854
<i>I am a celebrity</i>
<i>makeup artist.</i>

44:50.921 --> 44:56.026
And I was the last one
to film with Brittany.

44:56.093 --> 44:58.696
<i>When I got to that set,</i>
<i>I was told her husband</i>

44:58.762 --> 45:00.330
<i>was gonna be</i>
<i>her makeup artist.</i>

45:00.397 --> 45:01.765
<i>So it's day one.</i>

45:01.865 --> 45:05.903
I rushed to set just to find
a makeup disaster.

45:06.003 --> 45:07.271
[chuckles]

45:07.371 --> 45:10.774
<i>Simon had taken</i>
<i>a red tube of lipstick</i>

45:10.874 --> 45:13.444
<i>and had drawn lips</i>

45:13.544 --> 45:15.913
<i>outside her natural lip line</i>
<i>like a clown.</i>

45:16.013 --> 45:19.783
<i>Her blush was lopsided.</i>
<i>Her hair was greasy.</i>

45:19.883 --> 45:21.452
<i>Your job as a makeup artist</i>

45:21.552 --> 45:22.920
<i>is you're looking behind</i>
<i>the monitor</i>

45:23.020 --> 45:24.755
<i>to see if things</i>
<i>are changing.</i>

45:24.855 --> 45:27.357
<i>And watching Simon, he wasn't</i>
<i>looking in the monitor.</i>

45:27.424 --> 45:29.059
<i>He was looking straight ahead.</i>

45:29.126 --> 45:31.095
<i>He was in a catatonic state,</i>

45:31.195 --> 45:33.030
and I snapped my fingers
in front of his face

45:33.097 --> 45:35.766
to see if he'd react,
and he didn't even flinch.

45:35.866 --> 45:38.769
<i>I've been around</i>
<i>thousands of actors</i>

45:38.869 --> 45:41.438
<i>and never seen</i>
<i>someone that thin.</i>

45:41.538 --> 45:43.273
Her elbows.

45:43.373 --> 45:46.043
And getting out of a chair,
she looked like Bambi.

45:46.110 --> 45:48.112
<i>She just seemed</i>
<i>like she was in pain,</i>

45:48.212 --> 45:50.114
<i>especially when she moved.</i>

45:50.214 --> 45:51.982
<i>I think she was sick.</i>

45:52.082 --> 45:53.917
<i>She didn't care</i>
<i>if her hair was messed up.</i>

45:53.984 --> 45:55.385
<i>She didn't ask for a mirror.</i>

45:55.452 --> 45:57.654
<i>And that's unusual</i>
<i>in Hollywood.</i>

45:57.755 --> 46:00.958
<i>I just think she lost</i>
<i>the ability to care.</i>

46:01.058 --> 46:02.893
<i>She was a disaster</i>
<i>in her heart,</i>

46:02.960 --> 46:06.797
<i>and she was a disaster</i>
<i>emotionally and physically.</i>

46:06.897 --> 46:09.433
<i>[thunder rumbles]</i>

46:28.285 --> 46:31.455
<i>- We found that, evidently,</i>
<i>Simon got involved.</i>

46:31.522 --> 46:33.991
I don't know if he slapped
somebody or hit somebody,

46:34.091 --> 46:35.592
and she got fired.

46:35.659 --> 46:38.428
And that's why
they came back early.

46:38.495 --> 46:41.331
<i>- It was reported this week</i>
<i>that actress Brittany Murphy</i>

46:41.431 --> 46:43.500
was fired from her
upcoming film "The Caller"

46:43.600 --> 46:47.104
for being a detriment
to production and--oh, no.

46:47.171 --> 46:49.506
- Seth...
[laughter]

46:49.606 --> 46:50.841
- Brittany Murphy.

46:50.941 --> 46:52.543
- Yeah.

46:52.643 --> 46:54.278
They fired me.

46:54.344 --> 46:57.114
[chuckles]
Yeah.

46:57.181 --> 46:59.349
[laughter]

47:00.884 --> 47:05.289
<i>- In Puerto Rico, they became</i>
<i>ill with flu-like symptoms.</i>

47:05.355 --> 47:07.324
<i>They had flown back.</i>

47:07.391 --> 47:10.527
<i>Brittany started showing signs</i>
<i>of not feeling good,</i>

47:10.627 --> 47:12.996
<i>but they were treating</i>
<i>her sickness</i>

47:13.063 --> 47:15.699
with over-the-counter
medications.

47:15.799 --> 47:17.467
And, you know,
after a few days,

47:17.534 --> 47:20.204
if the over-the-counter
medications aren't working,

47:20.304 --> 47:25.209
you know, seek a professional
diagnosis on what's going on.

47:25.309 --> 47:27.911
<i>According to the information</i>
<i>that we got,</i>

47:28.011 --> 47:30.514
<i>it was kind of a habit</i>
<i>that Simon,</i>

47:30.581 --> 47:33.083
<i>he'd keep her up late,</i>
<i>they would order food in</i>

47:33.183 --> 47:34.718
<i>at 2:00 and 3:00</i>
<i>in the morning,</i>

47:34.818 --> 47:37.154
<i>and stay up</i>
<i>and watch television.</i>

47:37.221 --> 47:39.056
<i>She'd be exhausted</i>
<i>the next day</i>

47:39.156 --> 47:40.824
<i>and she wasn't getting</i>
<i>enough rest</i>

47:40.891 --> 47:43.060
<i>and her immune system</i>
<i>was dropping.</i>

47:43.160 --> 47:44.895
<i>He just was blanketed</i>
<i>around her</i>

47:44.995 --> 47:47.764
<i>and yet didn't remove</i>
<i>that blanket</i>

47:47.865 --> 47:51.068
<i>and seek medical attention</i>
<i>when she needed it.</i>

47:51.168 --> 47:52.736
<i>- She was a tiny girl.</i>

47:52.836 --> 47:55.372
<i>Your body can only</i>
<i>take so much.</i>

47:55.439 --> 47:57.908
[static crackling]

47:58.008 --> 48:00.911
<i>[light music]</i>

48:01.011 --> 48:03.247
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:03.347 --> 48:05.349
[indistinct chatter]

48:05.415 --> 48:07.517
- Don't move, ma'am.
Don't move.

48:07.584 --> 48:10.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

48:10.120 --> 48:13.423
<i>- The premiere of our film</i>
<i>was at the end of 2009.</i>

48:13.523 --> 48:16.193
When I saw her there,
she was extremely sweet,

48:16.260 --> 48:19.263
she was extremely proud.

48:19.363 --> 48:22.599
But she was also,
felt to me, extremely frail.

48:27.070 --> 48:30.707
- She embraced my hands
and her hands were shaky.

48:30.774 --> 48:33.277
She looked very,
very, very thin,

48:33.377 --> 48:35.379
like she had lost
a lot of weight.

48:39.149 --> 48:42.252
<i>Outside of that,</i>
<i>she wasn't acting strangely.</i>

48:42.319 --> 48:44.388
<i>She actually talked to me</i>
<i>about children that she was</i>

48:44.454 --> 48:46.890
<i>planning on having,</i>
<i>things that were very sweet.</i>

48:46.957 --> 48:50.761
<i>It felt really a lot more</i>
<i>like the person that I had met</i>

48:50.827 --> 48:52.896
when we were going into
this whole process.

48:52.963 --> 48:54.765
- Thank goodness
everyone was kind.

48:54.831 --> 48:58.802
No one generally
tends to be in a--

48:58.902 --> 49:03.173
on a set that's
an independent film,

49:03.273 --> 49:07.077
that has a short schedule
unless they really want to be.

49:07.144 --> 49:08.445
- What do you think--

49:08.512 --> 49:10.013
- Everyone
wanted to be there,

49:10.113 --> 49:11.915
and that was a pleasure.

49:11.982 --> 49:14.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

49:14.284 --> 49:16.253
<i>- Obviously,</i>
<i>the shoot experience</i>

49:16.320 --> 49:19.122
<i>was crazy and chaotic</i>
<i>and volatile at times.</i>

49:19.189 --> 49:21.858
<i>But I saw the person that</i>
<i>I had originally met with.</i>

49:21.959 --> 49:24.094
<i>It almost felt like it</i>
<i>came full circle.</i>

49:24.161 --> 49:25.829
<i>If we were like,</i>
<i>let's do another one,</i>

49:25.929 --> 49:28.966
I probably would have been
in this weird sort of,

49:29.032 --> 49:31.768
you know, euphoric space
with like,

49:31.835 --> 49:33.337
"Oh, this is great,
everything's good,

49:33.437 --> 49:35.539
and she's proud
and she's here to support."

49:35.639 --> 49:39.042
It turned out to be two weeks
before she passed away.

49:39.142 --> 49:43.146
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

49:43.213 --> 49:46.316
<i>- On a radio interview</i>
<i>in 2009,</i>

49:46.383 --> 49:50.954
somebody asked me to make
a prediction of who would die,

49:51.021 --> 49:53.223
what celebrity
would pass away.

49:53.323 --> 49:56.226
And I said Brittany Murphy.

49:58.328 --> 50:02.566
And all these years later now,
I just--

50:02.666 --> 50:06.837
I regret saying that, just
putting that energy out there.

50:06.903 --> 50:09.539
It's gross.

50:09.639 --> 50:11.341
Gross of the interviewer

50:11.408 --> 50:14.411
and gross of me
for giving a response.

50:16.513 --> 50:20.384
But that's definitely
telling of the time.

50:20.484 --> 50:25.555
2009, in many ways,
was a very gross time.

50:30.594 --> 50:32.062
<i>- [indistinct] 197.</i>

50:32.162 --> 50:33.563
<i>What's the address</i>
<i>of the emergency?</i>

50:33.663 --> 50:36.233
<i>- 1895 Rising Glen Road.</i>

50:36.333 --> 50:37.901
<i>- Tell me exactly</i>
<i>what happened.</i>

50:38.001 --> 50:40.370
<i>- My daughter's passed out.</i>

50:40.437 --> 50:42.906
<i>She's--they're doing</i>
<i>mouth to mouth.</i>

50:43.006 --> 50:44.541
<i>Please get here.</i>
<i>Please, please.</i>

50:44.608 --> 50:46.109
[wind howling]

50:46.209 --> 50:49.913
- My husband came in,
he said I have bad news.

50:50.013 --> 50:54.084
And I said,
"Did Brittany die?"

50:54.184 --> 50:56.253
And he said, "Yes."

50:59.222 --> 51:03.527
And I just felt so--
I felt bad for her.

51:03.593 --> 51:06.797
But I also felt,

51:06.897 --> 51:08.765
why didn't I
just go over there

51:08.865 --> 51:11.468
and knock on the door
all day long?

51:18.375 --> 51:21.745
And just have her hate me
or call the police

51:21.812 --> 51:25.382
but just knock on that door
and take her away.

51:25.449 --> 51:28.485
<i>[uneasy music]</i>

51:28.585 --> 51:31.721
<i>♪ ♪</i>

51:31.788 --> 51:34.958
<i>- You know, I ofttimes think</i>
<i>about Sharon too,</i>

51:35.058 --> 51:37.994
<i>just hoping she's okay,</i>

51:38.095 --> 51:39.663
<i>'cause when I had been</i>
<i>to the house,</i>

51:39.763 --> 51:41.631
<i>she would walk by</i>
<i>Brittany's clothes</i>

51:41.731 --> 51:43.300
<i>and she would smell</i>
<i>the clothes.</i>

51:43.400 --> 51:44.835
<i>But I remember</i>
<i>when she finally</i>

51:44.935 --> 51:46.636
<i>got all of Brittany's</i>
<i>clothes together</i>

51:46.736 --> 51:50.273
<i>and it filled up a whole room</i>
<i>and she had a sale.</i>

51:50.340 --> 51:51.908
<i>She sold them all.</i>

51:51.975 --> 51:55.579
<i>It took her about a year</i>
<i>to be able to do that,</i>

51:55.645 --> 51:57.180
<i>to come to terms with that.</i>

51:57.280 --> 51:58.782
The last I heard about Sharon,

51:58.849 --> 52:01.284
she was living
in Southern California,

52:01.351 --> 52:03.787
but very reclusive.

52:03.854 --> 52:06.756
She won't return emails
or phone calls.

52:06.823 --> 52:09.860
<i>Sharon was just heartbroken.</i>

52:13.363 --> 52:14.998
<i>- I had to accept</i>

52:15.098 --> 52:17.834
<i>there were no answers</i>
<i>for me to find in this.</i>

52:17.934 --> 52:21.171
So I had to kind of
step away from it.

52:22.272 --> 52:24.508
That was difficult
for me to do,

52:24.608 --> 52:25.976
but for a mother to accept

52:26.042 --> 52:29.045
that she might
not fully understand

52:29.146 --> 52:33.483
what happened to her son
can be quite devastating.

52:34.851 --> 52:38.822
<i>- I can't say why or what</i>
<i>happened in that house.</i>

52:38.889 --> 52:42.192
It became
a really awful tragedy

52:42.292 --> 52:44.361
that should never
have happened.

52:44.461 --> 52:49.966
But the reason why it happened
is very difficult to state.

52:50.967 --> 52:52.869
<i>- I believe</i>
<i>that Simon Monjack,</i>

52:52.969 --> 52:55.739
<i>even if he did not kill</i>
<i>Brittany Murphy,</i>

52:55.839 --> 52:57.974
he allowed her to die

52:58.041 --> 53:01.545
because he did not get her
to the doctor and get her help,

53:01.645 --> 53:05.882
and I believe that he did
the same thing to himself.

53:05.982 --> 53:08.318
Knowing that he needed
medical treatment,

53:08.385 --> 53:11.254
he didn't get it and he died.

53:11.354 --> 53:15.725
<i>He would rather be dead</i>
<i>than to be discovered</i>

53:15.825 --> 53:19.029
<i>as the con artist he was.</i>

53:20.096 --> 53:22.899
<i>- I think if it wasn't</i>
<i>for Simon Monjack,</i>

53:22.999 --> 53:24.734
<i>there's every chance</i>
<i>Brittany Murphy</i>

53:24.834 --> 53:26.403
<i>would still be alive.</i>

53:26.503 --> 53:28.338
It ultimately is like
a very banal story.

53:28.405 --> 53:30.340
It's just--it really
isn't a huge mystery.

53:30.407 --> 53:34.344
<i>It's just very simple,</i>
<i>a predator targeting someone</i>

53:34.411 --> 53:35.845
<i>at their most vulnerable.</i>

53:35.912 --> 53:38.281
<i>It was the perfect storm.</i>

53:38.381 --> 53:40.450
<i>- The cause of death</i>
<i>is not a mystery.</i>

53:40.550 --> 53:44.254
The mystery is why
didn't somebody catch it.

53:44.354 --> 53:46.723
Had they taken her to
the doctor a few days before,

53:46.790 --> 53:49.593
she'd still be alive.

53:49.693 --> 53:51.895
<i>There are some people</i>
<i>that they're not satisfied.</i>

53:51.962 --> 53:54.564
<i>You know, they think</i>
<i>maybe there's more.</i>

53:54.631 --> 53:56.900
<i>You just have</i>
<i>to go on the facts.</i>

53:59.436 --> 54:01.204
- Why do you just want
to settle for,

54:01.271 --> 54:04.808
"She died of pneumonia,
oh, well"?

54:04.908 --> 54:07.744
It just doesn't make sense.

54:07.811 --> 54:10.146
- Her death was not accidental,

54:10.247 --> 54:12.115
and her husband's
was not accidental.

54:12.215 --> 54:14.884
I believe they both
were targeted.

54:14.951 --> 54:18.255
- I think that their autopsies
were forged.

54:18.321 --> 54:19.456
- Something happened.

54:19.556 --> 54:21.625
Someone must have
bribed someone.

54:25.562 --> 54:28.732
- No, it just--it just
doesn't sound right.

54:28.798 --> 54:30.900
It doesn't even sound
like it adds up.

54:30.967 --> 54:33.937
It just--I'm sorry.
It don't add up.

54:34.004 --> 54:36.006
<i>[gentle music]</i>

54:36.106 --> 54:38.742
[indistinct radio chatter]

54:38.808 --> 54:45.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

54:46.249 --> 54:50.186
- Please.
Why can't you just let me die?

54:50.287 --> 54:57.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:05.769 --> 55:08.038
- We're gonna get out of here.

55:08.138 --> 55:09.673
<i>- Where are we gonna go?</i>

55:09.773 --> 55:14.010
- I don't know, someplace
where there's trees and sky,

55:14.110 --> 55:16.780
we can breathe
the fucking air.

55:16.846 --> 55:18.848
Some place that's
not so fucked up.

55:18.948 --> 55:26.022
<i>♪ ♪</i>

55:50.380 --> 55:51.881
Hi, my name
is Brittany Murphy,

55:51.981 --> 55:54.384
